<p>Position of point $A$, $B$, $C$, $D$, and $E$ in Fig. <a href="#fig:sfulm-1d-ABCDE-x-t">2</a> can be obtained by seeing its value at vertical axis $x$. The values have to match to the information provide by the text in the problem. Along horizontal axis $t$ the points are set in chronological order.</p>

<h2 id="function">Function</h2>
<p>Fig. <a href="#fig:sfulm-1d-ABCDE-x-t">2</a> we can obtain following function</p>

<p>\begin{equation}
\label{eqn:sfulm-points-ABCDE-x-t}
x(t) = \left\{
\begin{array}{lc}
t + 1,&amp; 0 \le t \lt 3, \newline
2t - 2,&amp; 3 \le t \lt 6, \newline
-t + 16,&amp; 6 \le t \lt 13, \newline
3t - 36,&amp; 13 \le t \lt 15,
\end{array}
\right.
\end{equation}</p>

<p>describing position of the object at every time $t$. Unit of $x$ is $\rm m$ and unit of $t$ is $\rm s$. Detail how to obtain Eqn. \eqref{eqn:sfulm-points-ABCDE-x-t} will be discuss in <a href="shift-xy-chart">shift x-y chart</a>. There is a lot of online chart tools that can be used to plot points [<a href="#ref1">1</a>] and even funtions [<a href="#ref2">2</a>].</p>

<h2 id="note">Note</h2>
<p>The term of step function uniform linear motion is not well known, and normally this type of motion is simply referred as ULM.</p>

<h2 id="exercises">Exercises</h2>
<ol>
  <li>Discuss which representation that you find helpful in visualizing information extracted from the problem. Explain why you like it.</li>
  <li>Think about displacement and distance. Find displacement and distance for time $0 \ {\rm s} \le t \lt 3 \ {\rm s}$, $3 \ {\rm s} \le t \lt 6 \ {\rm s}$, $6 \ {\rm s} \le t \lt 13 \ {\rm s}$,  and $13 \ {\rm s} \le t \lt 15 \ {\rm s}$.</li>
  <li>Find displacement and distance for time $0 \ {\rm s} \le t \lt 3 \ {\rm s}$, $0 \ {\rm s} \le t \lt 6 \ {\rm s}$, $0 \ {\rm s} \le t \lt 13 \ {\rm s}$, and $0 \ {\rm s} \le t \lt 15 \ {\rm s}$.</li>
  <li>Find the velocity $v$ in each time interval $0 \ {\rm s} \le t \lt 3 \ {\rm s}$, $3 \ {\rm s} \le t \lt 6 \ {\rm s}$, $6 \ {\rm s} \le t \lt 13 \ {\rm s}$,  and $13 \ {\rm s} \le t \lt 15 \ {\rm s}$,  and make a table and a function for it.</li>
  <li>Make your onw problem and visualize the information using table, sequence of pictures, graph, and function. Use at least four different points, e.g. $A$, $B$, $C$, $D$.</li>
</ol>

